// STUB ONLY - local editor assistance
//
// Why this file exists:
// - Prisma VSCode extension can lint one schema file without loading the
//   full merged schema graph used by CLI generation.
// - Portal schema references cross-module model `SysUser`, which is owned by
//   system schema. Isolated linting may report false "model not found" errors.
//
// Rules:
// - Keep stubs minimal and type-only.
// - No datasource/generator blocks here.
// - No real table mapping, indexes, or relations business logic.
// - This file is for editor DX only.
//
// Assembly behavior:
// - `_stubs.prisma` must never be used as source for final Prisma assembly.
// - Production schema still comes from generated files under
//   `apps/yishan-api/prisma/schema/`.
//
// Migration note:
// - If a module moves to an independent microservice/database later,
//   convert cross-service Prisma relations to ID references plus API/event
//   integration. Stub files can then be removed.

model SysUser {
  id Int @id
}
